Name: singleinstancestore
Type: SWITCH
Default-Value: 1
Last-Modified: 2.3.17

If enabled, imapd, lmtpd and nntpd attempt to only write one copy of a
message per partition and create hard links, resulting in a potentially
large disk savings. Duplicates that arise despite this (e.g. from
independent deliveries or per-user migrations) can be collapsed
afterwards with :cyrusman:`deduplicate(8)`.
